WEBVTT

00:00:00.968 --> 00:00:02.625
Our budget has been cut.

00:00:02.625 --> 00:00:05.838
Salary negotiations will become even tougher.

00:00:05.838 --> 00:00:09.081
Cut? By how much?

00:00:10.193 --> 00:00:11.776
30%.

00:00:11.776 --> 00:00:13.023
30%?

00:00:13.023 --> 00:00:15.608
That's an alarming number.

00:00:15.608 --> 00:00:18.786
We have no choice
but to sign contracts with this budget.

00:00:18.786 --> 00:00:21.552
We'll revise the salary plan
as soon as possible.

00:00:21.552 --> 00:00:25.785
Hold on a second. You agreed to this cut?

00:00:28.464 --> 00:00:31.481
A player's salary is their pride and joy!

00:00:31.481 --> 00:00:36.366
Exactly! If you cut salaries by 30%,
no one will sign!

00:00:36.366 --> 00:00:38.215
I'm absolutely against it.

00:00:38.215 --> 00:00:39.907
I'll even protest alone!

00:00:39.907 --> 00:00:41.357
I object!

00:00:41.357 --> 00:00:43.195
I object! I object!

00:00:43.195 --> 00:00:45.260
It won't make a difference
if you protest alone!

00:00:45.260 --> 00:00:50.098
The Dreams have been in last place
for four years straight.

00:00:50.098 --> 00:00:52.357
If they can't produce results,

00:00:53.250 --> 00:00:56.545
a salary reduction is unavoidable.

00:00:58.380 --> 00:01:00.233
This is...(Support Admin Watch on kissasia.cam or kisskh.org)

00:01:00.233 --> 00:01:03.570
A list of players to be released.

00:01:03.570 --> 00:01:04.628
Wait a sec, GM.

00:01:04.628 --> 00:01:07.283
You said you'd sign on the whole team!

00:01:07.283 --> 00:01:09.176
We can't lose ten whole players.

00:01:09.176 --> 00:01:12.044
We were hit with a 30% reduction.

00:01:13.712 --> 00:01:15.281
I'm doing what must be done.

00:01:15.281 --> 00:01:16.839
Oh, come on!

00:01:16.839 --> 00:01:19.208
I object! I object!

00:01:19.208 --> 00:01:20.595
I object!

00:01:20.595 --> 00:01:22.965
I won't move an inch from here!

00:01:22.965 --> 00:01:24.191
- Move.
- I object!

00:01:24.191 --> 00:01:25.913
- You're in the way.
- Let's fight together!

00:01:25.913 --> 00:01:27.746
Easier said than done...

00:01:27.746 --> 00:01:30.796
We object! We object!

00:01:43.198 --> 00:01:48.977
Negotiating with the players

00:01:48.977 --> 00:01:52.058
is one of your jobs.

00:01:52.058 --> 00:01:56.161
I cannot accept a 30% cut to our budget.

00:01:56.161 --> 00:01:59.225
It seems you weren't listening.

00:01:59.225 --> 00:02:01.267
I am not speaking my mind here.

00:02:01.267 --> 00:02:05.072
I am giving you an order, as the team owner.

00:02:15.424 --> 00:02:20.359
Our annual salary budget has been cut.

00:02:20.359 --> 00:02:23.131
We now have 30% less to work with.

00:02:23.131 --> 00:02:24.519
Seriously?

00:02:24.519 --> 00:02:27.565
This is unheard of.
It's downright terrifying.

00:02:27.565 --> 00:02:28.963
I'm against it. I object!

00:02:28.963 --> 00:02:30.970
Pay up!

00:02:30.970 --> 00:02:33.651
Don't cut our budget!

00:02:33.651 --> 00:02:35.781
Keep the dream in baseball!

00:02:35.781 --> 00:02:37.655
Quiet!

00:02:37.655 --> 00:02:42.177
We're here to have a meeting
because complaining gets us nowhere.

00:02:42.177 --> 00:02:43.990
Yes, sir.

00:02:44.854 --> 00:02:48.644
GM, how will we make this work?

00:02:48.644 --> 00:02:52.552
We must consider
releasing ten of our players.

00:02:55.444 --> 00:02:56.687
Ten of them?

00:02:56.687 --> 00:02:58.093
Oh, I don't want to see it.

00:02:58.093 --> 00:03:01.406
Reporters will hound us down
for releasing so many players.

00:03:01.406 --> 00:03:02.347
I object!

00:03:02.347 --> 00:03:03.928
- I also object.
- We object!

00:03:03.928 --> 00:03:07.806
Sir, Aikawa and Takasaki improve every year.

00:03:07.806 --> 00:03:08.888
Why would you let them go?

00:03:08.888 --> 00:03:10.513
- Exactly.
- They're right, GM.

00:03:10.513 --> 00:03:12.674
- Please reconsider your choices.
- That's right!

00:03:12.674 --> 00:03:14.178
How about releasing a veteran?

00:03:14.178 --> 00:03:15.646
- Like Hasebe...
- Exactly.

00:03:15.646 --> 00:03:18.217
- No, we can't let him go either.
- We can't let Hasebe go!

00:03:18.217 --> 00:03:20.680
And we can't lose the good-looking Senoo.

00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:23.118
His uniform sales are among the highest.

00:03:23.118 --> 00:03:24.619
We will suffer terrible losses!

00:03:24.619 --> 00:03:26.713
So we're choosing based on looks now?

00:03:26.713 --> 00:03:28.128
Your bias is shining through.

00:03:28.128 --> 00:03:29.165
I don't like that.

00:03:29.165 --> 00:03:32.487
Oh, quit whining! I'm talking about sales!

00:03:32.487 --> 00:03:33.753
Don't choose by looks!

00:03:33.753 --> 00:03:35.682
- You're being biased!
- Shut up, you monkeys!

00:03:35.682 --> 00:03:37.354
- A player's abilities are...
- No bias allowed.

00:03:37.354 --> 00:03:38.660
- I'm talking about sales!
- Can we not?

00:03:38.660 --> 00:03:41.066
More importantly.

00:03:41.066 --> 00:03:44.253
Our team already suffers
from a lack of players.

00:03:44.253 --> 00:03:48.091
Dismiss 10, and we'd only have 60 remaining.

00:03:48.091 --> 00:03:51.344
If we see many injuries,
would we even survive a season?

00:03:53.468 --> 00:03:55.048
Manager.

00:03:56.224 --> 00:03:57.809
No.

00:04:01.838 --> 00:04:05.843
So you all need the pitchers,
Aikawa and Takasaki.

00:04:08.093 --> 00:04:11.549
What about our other pitcher, Senoo?

00:04:17.081 --> 00:04:18.763
And Ebata?

00:04:27.304 --> 00:04:30.424
These players trust in my every direction.

00:04:30.424 --> 00:04:33.636
They all follow my lead.

00:04:34.854 --> 00:04:37.015
I cannot choose one over the other.

00:04:39.943 --> 00:04:42.645
May I be excused?

00:04:45.941 --> 00:04:48.499
Yes. Go ahead.

00:04:52.724 --> 00:04:55.411
No, wait, wait, wait...

00:04:55.411 --> 00:04:57.302
Don't just let him leave.

00:04:57.302 --> 00:04:58.813
He's the manager!

00:04:58.813 --> 00:04:59.582
I will continue.

00:04:59.582 --> 00:05:03.688
You gotta listen to me, GM!

00:05:03.688 --> 00:05:05.550
This is hopeless!

00:05:05.550 --> 00:05:07.403
I'm going back to protesting.

00:05:08.242 --> 00:05:09.749
Don't cut the players!

00:05:09.749 --> 00:05:11.225
Don't cut the players!

00:05:11.225 --> 00:05:12.610
Give us the money!

00:05:12.610 --> 00:05:14.148
- Give us the money!
- Quiet!

00:05:14.148 --> 00:05:15.649
Don't cut the players!

00:05:15.649 --> 00:05:17.544
- Give us the money!
- Right now!

00:05:17.544 --> 00:05:20.120
Quiet!

00:05:20.120 --> 00:05:22.736
Now back to your seats.

00:05:22.736 --> 00:05:24.831
- No!
- We'll keep at it all night!

00:05:24.831 --> 00:05:27.634
What about the pitcher, Kijima?

00:05:27.634 --> 00:05:29.104
[Yuuki Kijima]

00:05:34.890 --> 00:05:36.637
May I dismiss him?

00:05:36.637 --> 00:05:38.524
Now hold on a second.

00:05:38.524 --> 00:05:42.172
Kijima is a star.
He was named a class-A pitcher 6 years ago.

00:05:42.172 --> 00:05:46.865
Then all those who believe Kijima
ought to stay, raise your hands.

00:05:54.938 --> 00:05:56.979
All agree to dismissing him.

00:06:12.032 --> 00:06:13.670
Alright.

00:06:14.894 --> 00:06:16.667
Right then.

00:06:16.667 --> 00:06:18.793
- I'm home.
- Welcome back.

00:06:18.793 --> 00:06:20.348
Up five.

00:06:20.348 --> 00:06:23.088
- Daddy!
- Hana!

00:06:23.088 --> 00:06:24.421
What'd you do today?

00:06:24.421 --> 00:06:26.926
- I played in the mud!
- In the mud? Wild.

00:06:26.926 --> 00:06:29.525
- Must've been tough, huh?
- It was.

00:06:29.525 --> 00:06:33.931
She might make a great infielder though.

00:06:35.372 --> 00:06:37.854
When do you think
the salary negotiations will be?

00:06:37.854 --> 00:06:39.993
I think it's coming up.

00:06:41.106 --> 00:06:43.256
Will your estimate go down?

00:06:43.256 --> 00:06:44.776
Probably.

00:06:46.765 --> 00:06:49.929
Well, you're already earning plenty.

00:06:49.929 --> 00:06:52.688
Don't worry, Daddy's still got lots to earn!

00:06:52.688 --> 00:06:55.707
Oh, that's reassuring.

00:06:55.707 --> 00:06:57.644
- Daddy, look!
- Huh? What?

00:06:57.644 --> 00:06:59.033
- You drew this for me?
- Yeah!

00:06:59.033 --> 00:07:00.500
Is this your Daddy?

00:07:00.500 --> 00:07:02.524
No, that's the ball!

00:07:02.524 --> 00:07:03.770
- The ball?
- Yeah.

00:07:03.770 --> 00:07:06.899
Thanks, Champ. Let me return the favor.

00:07:06.899 --> 00:07:10.540
I will proceed with Kijima's dismissal.

00:07:10.540 --> 00:07:14.223
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

00:07:14.223 --> 00:07:19.389
Akito and I carefully analyzed
our autumn camp practice games.

00:07:19.389 --> 00:07:24.405
Kijima can still be a valuable asset.

00:07:24.405 --> 00:07:26.225
Nice play, youngster!

00:07:26.225 --> 00:07:33.761
Kijima pitches to the batter
in a way that makes the ball hard to hit.

00:07:33.761 --> 00:07:36.409
He keeps extra base hits to a minimum.

00:07:36.409 --> 00:07:38.370
Your thoughts, GM?

00:07:39.724 --> 00:07:42.943
We will negotiate
with all players on the team.

00:07:42.943 --> 00:07:46.371
- Yes! The protest worked!
- That's great!

00:07:47.346 --> 00:07:52.853
Our GM has given us the right guidance.

00:07:52.853 --> 00:07:55.691
Now we simply walk the path of light.

00:07:55.691 --> 00:07:56.882
You sound terrifying.

00:07:56.882 --> 00:07:59.851
Please, no deifying the GM.

00:07:59.851 --> 00:08:01.482
So what do we do now?

00:08:01.482 --> 00:08:04.146
We can't lower everyone's pay.

00:08:04.146 --> 00:08:05.538
Not now, alright?

00:08:05.538 --> 00:08:07.235
Let us celebrate a bit!

00:08:07.235 --> 00:08:08.948
- Yeah, Osachan!
- Read the room.

00:08:08.948 --> 00:08:11.354
- Osachan.
- We'll start by lowering your salary.

00:08:11.354 --> 00:08:13.232
The players will simply have to take it.

00:08:13.232 --> 00:08:17.780
Are we really cutting 30% from everyone?

00:08:17.780 --> 00:08:20.588
We can't give any less
to players with low salaries.

00:08:20.588 --> 00:08:22.708
- I will reassess our salary criteria.
- What?

00:08:22.708 --> 00:08:27.973
You sure love your controversial ideas, GM.

00:08:27.973 --> 00:08:32.167
The only time a decision of mine
was met with no backlash...

00:08:33.279 --> 00:08:36.037
was when I changed the position of our vases.

00:08:37.832 --> 00:08:39.909
- It's not funny.
- Huh?

00:08:39.909 --> 00:08:41.768
We will base each player's salary

00:08:41.768 --> 00:08:44.793
on their performance from this year alone.

00:08:44.793 --> 00:08:47.900
That's a risky move, GM.

00:08:47.900 --> 00:08:52.178
You're going to be met
with waves of backlash.

00:08:53.307 --> 00:08:55.537
What's about to begin

00:08:55.537 --> 00:09:00.762
is a life-or-death battle
between the players, and management.

00:09:28.539 --> 00:09:32.194
I see the store's really thriving now.

00:09:32.194 --> 00:09:35.073
It's about damn time.

00:09:35.073 --> 00:09:37.353
What'd you think? Good, right?

00:09:37.353 --> 00:09:39.493
Super good. Delicious!

00:09:39.493 --> 00:09:42.707
- He's practically fluent.
- Yeah, you're good.

00:09:43.956 --> 00:09:45.083
- Ushiyama.
- Yeah?

00:09:45.083 --> 00:09:47.887
You look happier these days.

00:09:47.887 --> 00:09:50.018
You think?

00:09:50.018 --> 00:09:51.204
Nah, maybe not.

00:09:51.204 --> 00:09:52.828
Make up your mind.

00:09:54.955 --> 00:09:57.777
So, what're your plans next season?

00:09:59.420 --> 00:10:01.865
I'm going to keep playing.

00:10:01.865 --> 00:10:03.925
Did you already negotiate your salary?

00:10:05.081 --> 00:10:09.711
Not yet. I suspect it'll go down though.

00:10:10.712 --> 00:10:14.399
You earned... What, 40 million last year?

00:10:15.181 --> 00:10:16.483
- 40?
- 30, 30...

00:10:16.483 --> 00:10:18.170
- Right, 30 million.
- Wow...

00:10:19.270 --> 00:10:20.892
Hey, quit it.

00:10:20.892 --> 00:10:22.732
Yeah, you're first pick of the draft.

00:10:22.732 --> 00:10:23.578
Exactly.
[Lim Min Jong - Pitcher]

00:10:23.578 --> 00:10:27.499
You're getting 100 million
from the signing bonus alone.

00:10:35.333 --> 00:10:38.943
So this year you'd get about...

00:10:40.370 --> 00:10:42.322
20 million, give or take?

00:10:44.663 --> 00:10:46.727
Something like that.

00:10:46.727 --> 00:10:49.933
Why not retire
and start a restaurant already?

00:10:53.000 --> 00:10:55.315
Sawada is back on the team.

00:10:55.315 --> 00:10:58.171
And now we've got Min Jong, too.

00:10:59.906 --> 00:11:03.581
I still want to win.

00:11:07.212 --> 00:11:09.698
You look raring to go.

00:11:09.698 --> 00:11:11.050
I'm embarrassed.

00:11:11.050 --> 00:11:12.336
Alright!

00:11:12.336 --> 00:11:14.088
- We're going another round!
- Another one?

00:11:14.088 --> 00:11:15.817
- Another one!
- Alright.

00:11:16.902 --> 00:11:20.082
One, two, Dreams!

00:11:20.082 --> 00:11:21.764
Yeah!

00:11:21.764 --> 00:11:24.794
[Job Search Results]

00:11:24.794 --> 00:11:25.933
I'm home.

00:11:25.933 --> 00:11:28.667
Yeah, welcome back.

00:11:30.938 --> 00:11:34.642
Woah. You're actually looking for a job.

00:11:34.642 --> 00:11:36.209
Finally ready to work?

00:11:36.209 --> 00:11:39.841
Yeah. It's hard to find a good place, though.

00:11:39.841 --> 00:11:41.872
You're being too picky.

00:11:41.872 --> 00:11:43.933
I wouldn't want to take the plunge,

00:11:43.933 --> 00:11:47.720
only to lose 20% of my bonus again, you know?

00:11:48.388 --> 00:11:50.733
I'm getting angry just thinking about it.

00:11:50.733 --> 00:11:51.897
Sorry.

00:11:51.897 --> 00:11:54.216
Why are you apologizing?

00:11:54.216 --> 00:11:58.961
If anything, given my background,
shouldn't I be earning more?

00:11:58.961 --> 00:12:01.776
A salary is a symbol of sincerity.

00:12:04.144 --> 00:12:06.862
You're entirely right.

00:12:06.862 --> 00:12:08.673
That's it.

00:12:08.673 --> 00:12:09.991
I'm done searching for jobs.

00:12:09.991 --> 00:12:11.220
I'm sorry, keep going.

00:12:11.220 --> 00:12:12.632
- No, thanks.
- I said I'm sorry!

00:12:12.632 --> 00:12:15.845
- It's relaxation time.
- Back to routine already?

00:12:15.845 --> 00:12:18.486
The eat-and-sleep competition begins!

00:12:18.486 --> 00:12:20.863
I never signed up for that.

00:12:20.863 --> 00:12:23.221
Hey, bring me a beer. Please?

00:12:24.132 --> 00:12:25.274
Beer, beer.

00:12:25.274 --> 00:12:26.157
I'm going to sleep.

00:12:26.157 --> 00:12:30.080
Aw, already? I really wanted a beer...

00:12:37.144 --> 00:12:39.694
[YAOSHIMA Holdings]

00:12:45.500 --> 00:12:48.197
Reducing their annual salary, eh?

00:12:48.197 --> 00:12:50.892
Great idea.

00:12:50.892 --> 00:12:56.231
Any surplus will be diverted
to our Shopping Mall Division.

00:12:56.231 --> 00:12:59.322
Suppressing the team's deficit,
and paving the way for its dissolution.

00:12:59.322 --> 00:13:01.821
I see! Perfect!

00:13:01.821 --> 00:13:02.953
Thank you, sir.

00:13:02.953 --> 00:13:05.366
Will it really go so smoothly though?

00:13:05.366 --> 00:13:07.430
That GM loves to get in your way.

00:13:07.430 --> 00:13:08.936
Shut up.

00:13:08.936 --> 00:13:11.510
Shut up your mouth.

00:13:11.510 --> 00:13:14.025
Shut up your mouth!

00:13:14.708 --> 00:13:15.860
Don't be such a wet blanket.

00:13:15.860 --> 00:13:17.406
My apologies.

00:13:17.406 --> 00:13:18.740
Not to worry, sir.

00:13:18.740 --> 00:13:22.982
Humans are powerless
against financial prowess.

00:13:30.975 --> 00:13:33.648
Can I call in Iwata?

00:13:33.648 --> 00:13:34.813
Please do.

00:13:34.813 --> 00:13:36.986
We're starting with a tough one.

00:13:36.986 --> 00:13:38.723
Tough, indeed.

00:13:40.584 --> 00:13:42.935
Come on in.

00:13:46.895 --> 00:13:48.292
Morning!

00:13:48.292 --> 00:13:50.134
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

00:13:50.937 --> 00:13:52.336
Please, have a seat.

00:13:58.213 --> 00:13:59.712
Let's get right to it.

00:13:59.712 --> 00:14:02.955
Mr. Iwata, your salary for next year...

00:14:04.302 --> 00:14:07.969
To quote the great Katsuya Nomura,

00:14:07.969 --> 00:14:12.736
the catcher is like a manager on the field.

00:14:14.931 --> 00:14:18.920
That's how important we are to the team.

00:14:18.920 --> 00:14:21.849
With that in mind, let's get talking.

00:14:23.157 --> 00:14:25.940
You missed many games this year.

00:14:25.940 --> 00:14:28.549
As such, a salary cut will be unavoidable.

00:14:28.549 --> 00:14:30.998
What do you mean?

00:14:31.655 --> 00:14:34.469
- This year's results...
- Next season's salary

00:14:34.469 --> 00:14:37.683
includes expectations for the future, no?

00:14:37.683 --> 00:14:40.825
A player ought to make negotiations

00:14:40.825 --> 00:14:43.521
based on their performance in the year.

00:14:45.082 --> 00:14:47.050
Alright, fine.

00:14:47.851 --> 00:14:49.649
You make a point.

00:14:49.649 --> 00:14:54.733
I missed games earlier this season
because I got injured.

00:14:54.733 --> 00:14:57.685
But look at my performance
in the latter half of the year.

00:14:57.685 --> 00:15:01.514
My OPS is number one
among defensive catchers.

00:15:02.233 --> 00:15:05.260
As embarrassed as I am to say this myself,

00:15:05.260 --> 00:15:11.328
the fans call me their, "last hope".
[OPS: sum of player's on-base% and slugging%]

00:15:14.084 --> 00:15:15.620
GM.

00:15:17.524 --> 00:15:20.794
I heard you're an amateur in baseball.

00:15:20.794 --> 00:15:22.147
That is entirely irrelevant now.

00:15:22.147 --> 00:15:24.604
Allow me to inform the uninformed.

00:15:25.317 --> 00:15:29.167
I don't have a chronic illness.

00:15:31.362 --> 00:15:34.431
I was injured during a game.

00:15:34.431 --> 00:15:37.316
It was an unavoidable accident.

00:15:38.228 --> 00:15:40.276
Was it really?

00:15:40.276 --> 00:15:41.673
What?

00:15:41.673 --> 00:15:45.453
Was it truly unavoidable?

00:15:49.906 --> 00:15:54.303
I always fight for the team.
What're you trying to get at?

00:15:54.303 --> 00:15:58.186
You struggle with maintaining a fit body.

00:15:59.057 --> 00:16:02.135
The weight you gain
from binge-drinking and eating

00:16:02.135 --> 00:16:04.272
is putting strain on your knees.

00:16:04.272 --> 00:16:08.571
It seems you're also neglecting
your post-game cool down drills.

00:16:09.764 --> 00:16:13.639
Our assessment was made
after taking all this into account.

00:16:20.051 --> 00:16:21.491
200 million.

00:16:22.686 --> 00:16:25.370
I'm tired of bargaining,
so let's just go with this amount.

00:16:26.705 --> 00:16:28.380
[60 million]

00:16:28.380 --> 00:16:30.127
That is...

00:16:31.619 --> 00:16:32.989
quite the unexpected amount.

00:16:32.989 --> 00:16:35.207
I'd say it's more than reasonable.

00:16:36.329 --> 00:16:39.960
I'm the best defensive catcher in Japan.

00:16:39.960 --> 00:16:42.590
I think you're getting a bargain.

00:16:46.123 --> 00:16:50.212
We wouldn't agree.

00:16:57.784 --> 00:16:59.305
I'm leaving.

00:17:03.770 --> 00:17:06.816
See? Told you.

00:17:06.816 --> 00:17:09.132
It's only the first guy,
and we're already stumbling.

00:17:13.435 --> 00:17:14.382
What?

00:17:14.382 --> 00:17:17.167
Next up is our shortstop, Nara.

00:17:17.167 --> 00:17:18.524
What kind of player is he?

00:17:18.524 --> 00:17:21.356
He's a kind and friendly guy.

00:17:21.356 --> 00:17:24.292
He understands the team's circumstances well.

00:17:24.292 --> 00:17:26.482
It'll go smoothly.

00:17:35.511 --> 00:17:39.438
After that day,
I thought I'd spend my days relaxing,

00:17:39.438 --> 00:17:41.749
but my cute junior was in a pickle.

00:17:41.749 --> 00:17:44.514
I couldn't just leave him be.

00:17:47.419 --> 00:17:49.097
Excuse me.

00:17:50.568 --> 00:17:54.316
The players summarize their performance data,

00:17:54.316 --> 00:18:01.686
but once they sit down for negotiations,
their minds go blank.

00:18:04.320 --> 00:18:09.826
The players wanted an agent they could trust.

00:18:09.826 --> 00:18:12.838
I had no choice but to take up the mantle.

00:18:12.838 --> 00:18:16.509
Let's have a constructive discussion.
For both our sakes.

00:18:16.509 --> 00:18:20.686
Only an attorney can accompany players
to negotiations. Please leave.

00:18:20.686 --> 00:18:23.013
Let's not get so formal, eh?

00:18:23.013 --> 00:18:24.688
I know how business works here.

00:18:24.688 --> 00:18:27.053
Negotiations will go quick if I'm here.

00:18:27.823 --> 00:18:28.855
Please leave.

00:18:28.855 --> 00:18:33.852
GM, you're lowering players' salaries
because the team finished last, right?

00:18:33.852 --> 00:18:37.637
Team performance is irrelevant
to individual salary negotiations.

00:18:37.637 --> 00:18:40.255
Hey, now. Was that the case last year too?

00:18:41.375 --> 00:18:42.167
Yes.

00:18:42.167 --> 00:18:45.915
Well, that's just awful.

00:18:45.915 --> 00:18:52.193
You're not thinking of offering him
a measly 44 million, are you?

00:18:53.004 --> 00:18:54.844
[44 million yen]

00:18:57.355 --> 00:18:59.027
That's a very specific amount.

00:18:59.027 --> 00:19:00.710
What?

00:19:00.710 --> 00:19:02.081
Did I hit the bull's-eye?

00:19:02.081 --> 00:19:03.420
No.

00:19:03.420 --> 00:19:06.533
I'm glad I didn't.

00:19:06.533 --> 00:19:12.991
Our Nara is too kind, so he's easily swayed.

00:19:12.991 --> 00:19:16.035
Please offer him a reasonable amount, yeah?

00:19:17.383 --> 00:19:19.828
Seems like this is gonna take a while.

00:19:19.828 --> 00:19:23.181
We haven't even had lunch yet.

00:19:23.181 --> 00:19:24.798
How about this?

00:19:26.660 --> 00:19:29.056
Here, teriyaki flavor.

00:19:29.773 --> 00:19:32.161
Miyahara.

00:19:32.161 --> 00:19:34.461
Grab us three iced coffees.

00:19:34.461 --> 00:19:36.002
Pardon?

00:19:36.002 --> 00:19:37.258
Sir, you're being awfully rude.

00:19:37.258 --> 00:19:40.566
Right, my bad, my bad.

00:19:40.566 --> 00:19:42.982
Grab a 'something-ccino' for yourself, too.

00:19:42.982 --> 00:19:45.484
I suspect we'll remain at a stalemate today.

00:19:45.484 --> 00:19:46.803
Please leave.

00:19:46.803 --> 00:19:49.539
Oh, that's right.

00:19:49.539 --> 00:19:51.823
Please don't misunderstand.

00:19:51.823 --> 00:19:56.647
This isn't revenge for being falsely accused.

00:19:56.647 --> 00:19:58.989
You're keeping our other players waiting.

00:19:58.989 --> 00:20:01.889
You mean Kato, Shirasaki, and Nojima?

00:20:04.614 --> 00:20:08.301
We're here to represent those three, too.

00:20:08.301 --> 00:20:10.544
Shall we continue?

00:20:10.544 --> 00:20:12.414
[Nara, Kato, Shirasaki, Nojima]

00:20:12.414 --> 00:20:14.287
Miyahara, three iced coffees.

00:20:14.287 --> 00:20:16.815
Don't forget the 'something-ccino'.

00:20:23.194 --> 00:20:24.384
Yes, exactly.

00:20:24.384 --> 00:20:27.436
Find us a good place, you hear?

00:20:27.436 --> 00:20:30.432
One that offers great wine. Yeah.

00:20:30.432 --> 00:20:33.083
He's very particular.

00:20:33.083 --> 00:20:34.761
That's right.

00:20:34.761 --> 00:20:36.610
Yeah, I'm counting on you.

00:20:37.448 --> 00:20:39.652
Excuse me, I'll call you back.

00:20:41.777 --> 00:20:44.325
What's with the stare, sir?

00:20:44.325 --> 00:20:48.944
The worst kind of trash
is someone who betrays their comrades.

00:20:50.887 --> 00:20:54.039
I don't know what you're talking about.

00:20:59.743 --> 00:21:01.749
You still don't get it?

00:21:15.455 --> 00:21:18.560
Did Assistant Director Kikuchi
leak our assessment?

00:21:18.560 --> 00:21:19.859
Yes.

00:21:20.571 --> 00:21:22.244
Let's move on.

00:21:22.244 --> 00:21:24.469
Right.

00:21:24.469 --> 00:21:27.096
Okay! Next up is a veteran.

00:21:27.096 --> 00:21:29.488
Let's get to it!

00:21:29.488 --> 00:21:32.887
Until last year, players with families
were given a priority.

00:21:32.887 --> 00:21:36.765
But this year, we'll judge them
solely on individual ability.

00:21:36.765 --> 00:21:38.336
Hold on a second, GM.

00:21:38.336 --> 00:21:42.131
Isn't that a bit too cold?
They have families.

00:21:42.131 --> 00:21:44.383
We hope to sign everyone on.

00:21:45.607 --> 00:21:47.280
I'm doing what must be done.

00:21:47.280 --> 00:21:48.898
Yes, I understand, GM.

00:21:48.898 --> 00:21:50.765
- But!
- Miyahara!

00:21:50.765 --> 00:21:51.927
Ow!

00:21:51.927 --> 00:21:53.667
Let's prepare ourselves.

00:21:54.425 --> 00:21:56.320
Preparedness injected.

00:21:56.320 --> 00:21:58.054
Alright.

00:21:58.054 --> 00:21:59.975
Who are we seeing next?

00:22:00.847 --> 00:22:02.926
Kijima.

00:22:14.027 --> 00:22:15.924
Though you are a veteran,

00:22:15.924 --> 00:22:20.419
our assessment for this year
will be based solely on your performance.

00:22:21.075 --> 00:22:24.665
Understood. I'm prepared to hear the number.

00:22:31.299 --> 00:22:33.357
How does 8 million yen sound?

00:22:41.713 --> 00:22:46.935
You can't cut a salary
by more than 25%, can you?

00:22:48.914 --> 00:22:51.074
Without the players' consent?

00:22:52.614 --> 00:22:54.236
No.

00:22:58.759 --> 00:23:01.071
Did you have a desired amount in mind?

00:23:01.071 --> 00:23:02.594
Oh, no...

00:23:05.765 --> 00:23:07.441
It's just...

00:23:09.321 --> 00:23:11.587
Please give me time to think.

00:23:19.970 --> 00:23:22.112
Eight million?

00:23:24.828 --> 00:23:27.315
They're essentially telling you to quit.

00:23:27.315 --> 00:23:30.364
Well...

00:23:32.022 --> 00:23:34.164
Want to help run my restaurant?

00:23:34.164 --> 00:23:35.867
Huh?

00:23:35.867 --> 00:23:38.397
I'm opening a new branch this year.

00:23:38.397 --> 00:23:42.707
Juggle that with teaching baseball,
and you'd make 10 million a year.

00:23:46.672 --> 00:23:49.799
Isn't your body feeling its age about now?

00:23:50.808 --> 00:23:52.688
Well...

00:23:52.688 --> 00:23:55.427
Give it some thought, yeah?

00:23:55.427 --> 00:23:56.899
I appreciate it.

00:23:56.899 --> 00:23:58.495
- Thank you.
- Anytime.

00:23:58.495 --> 00:23:59.891
Now eat up.

00:23:59.891 --> 00:24:01.446
- Right.
- Here.

00:24:01.446 --> 00:24:03.316
- Today's beef tongue is delicious.
- Really?

00:24:03.316 --> 00:24:05.185
- Yeah.
- I'll give it a try.

00:24:07.605 --> 00:24:09.768
Kurokawa, back then and now,

00:24:09.768 --> 00:24:14.375
you've always reminded me
of crystal clear water.

00:24:16.015 --> 00:24:18.250
What do you mean?

00:24:18.250 --> 00:24:22.087
On the field,
you were the reliable third batter up.

00:24:22.087 --> 00:24:24.503
After retiring, you became Scouting Director.

00:24:24.503 --> 00:24:28.630
And now, you've become an independent agent.

00:24:30.113 --> 00:24:34.534
You mold to any role like water.

00:24:34.534 --> 00:24:37.749
And because you're so clear,

00:24:37.749 --> 00:24:41.593
you hide nothing from others.

00:24:46.108 --> 00:24:50.098
Do you know
why the GM tries to sign everyone on,

00:24:50.098 --> 00:24:55.557
despite the odds stacked against him?

00:24:56.528 --> 00:24:59.542
Is it because he's an amateur?

00:24:59.542 --> 00:25:01.566
No, no.

00:25:01.566 --> 00:25:07.549
It's to flaunt his own beliefs.

00:25:07.549 --> 00:25:10.030
To those around him, that is.

00:25:12.258 --> 00:25:18.532
Belief is meant to be broken, broken...

00:25:20.948 --> 00:25:22.801
And broken again.

00:25:24.745 --> 00:25:28.436
You must break the pen you're signing with.

00:25:28.436 --> 00:25:34.015
Do so, and his beliefs will break as well.

00:25:39.496 --> 00:25:44.506
If negotiations drag on,
camp will be canceled.

00:25:44.506 --> 00:25:47.667
If it continues into the season,

00:25:48.427 --> 00:25:50.843
not only will victory prove to be a struggle,

00:25:50.843 --> 00:25:55.970
but the team's very existence
will be at risk.

00:25:57.038 --> 00:25:59.316
And if that happens,

00:25:59.316 --> 00:26:04.018
his resignation will be the price to pay.

00:26:05.453 --> 00:26:07.805
Sounds like trouble.

00:26:10.586 --> 00:26:18.009
I only hope the next GM
will be someone as clear as water.

00:26:20.353 --> 00:26:25.476
We'll wash it all clean
with a douse of water.

00:26:36.759 --> 00:26:38.988
I sense your impatience.

00:26:41.030 --> 00:26:43.015
Where is the attorney?

00:26:43.015 --> 00:26:47.111
She will be joining us remotely today.

00:26:48.083 --> 00:26:51.567
That's fine.
But you must leave, Mr. Kurokawa.

00:26:51.567 --> 00:26:52.911
Those are the rules.

00:26:52.911 --> 00:26:57.069
Stop babbling and tell me his offer.

00:27:00.572 --> 00:27:02.316
60 million yen.

00:27:08.359 --> 00:27:11.179
I don't think we'll be reaching an agreement.

00:27:13.425 --> 00:27:15.761
That's a shame.

00:27:15.761 --> 00:27:17.941
I'll close this for now.

00:27:20.362 --> 00:27:23.072
I understand you're a busy man, GM.

00:27:23.072 --> 00:27:26.395
Maybe you're not thinking so clearly?

00:27:26.395 --> 00:27:30.512
Give it some more thought.

00:27:31.234 --> 00:27:33.015
Kurokawa...

00:27:35.323 --> 00:27:36.781
Sir.

00:27:40.346 --> 00:27:43.341
I won't offer this amount next time.

00:27:43.341 --> 00:27:45.026
Do you understand?

00:27:45.906 --> 00:27:47.779
If you'll excuse me.

00:27:55.941 --> 00:27:58.281
A player would sign for that amount.

00:27:58.281 --> 00:28:01.379
He only wants to prolong the negotiations.

00:28:06.378 --> 00:28:07.711
GM.

00:28:07.711 --> 00:28:11.758
Iwata wants to speak again.

00:28:13.608 --> 00:28:17.335
Also, regarding Mr. Kijima's negotiation.

00:28:17.335 --> 00:28:20.502
Can I try handling it?

00:28:23.748 --> 00:28:25.442
Go ahead.

00:28:27.341 --> 00:28:29.197
Thank you!

00:28:29.197 --> 00:28:30.722
I'm off!

00:28:32.763 --> 00:28:34.187
Excuse me.

00:28:34.187 --> 00:28:35.271
Ouch!

00:28:35.271 --> 00:28:37.033
You alright?

00:28:37.033 --> 00:28:38.220
I'm fine.

00:28:38.220 --> 00:28:39.557
Just cut myself with the knife.

00:28:39.557 --> 00:28:41.192
Lemme see that.

00:28:41.192 --> 00:28:43.089
Yikes.

00:28:43.878 --> 00:28:46.154
- Here's a bandage.
- Hello.

00:28:48.035 --> 00:28:49.905
Oh...

00:28:49.905 --> 00:28:54.112
The Dreams still need you, Mr. Kijima.

00:28:56.770 --> 00:28:59.299
I'm glad you say that,

00:28:59.299 --> 00:29:00.888
but I'm already...

00:29:01.676 --> 00:29:03.322
Truth be told,

00:29:04.784 --> 00:29:10.257
I only became a baseball fan
after joining the company.

00:29:10.257 --> 00:29:13.334
I studied up on the team's history, too.

00:29:13.334 --> 00:29:18.067
Six years ago, the Dreams came in 2nd place.

00:29:18.067 --> 00:29:20.640
You remember, right?

00:29:20.640 --> 00:29:22.049
Of course.

00:29:22.049 --> 00:29:26.153
The Dreams owe that 2nd place
to your pitching, Mr. Kijima.

00:29:31.777 --> 00:29:33.911
Maybe that was my peak.

00:29:34.548 --> 00:29:36.146
Huh?

00:29:36.146 --> 00:29:39.350
The time to retire always comes.

00:29:42.405 --> 00:29:45.726
I ought to have retired back then.

00:29:45.726 --> 00:29:47.745
No, no, no, that's not true!

00:29:47.745 --> 00:29:50.152
I wanted to leave without shame.

00:29:51.421 --> 00:29:54.364
To leave reluctantly, but with a whole heart.

00:30:02.607 --> 00:30:04.591
This negotiation.

00:30:06.198 --> 00:30:07.970
This amount.

00:30:10.097 --> 00:30:12.382
It's a notice of dismissal, isn't it?

00:30:17.864 --> 00:30:20.195
I'm retiring.

00:30:20.195 --> 00:30:21.653
Huh?

00:30:29.872 --> 00:30:32.487
Ow, ouch!

00:30:32.487 --> 00:30:34.393
And it's over.

00:30:35.030 --> 00:30:37.794
We'll treat your thumb next week.

00:30:37.794 --> 00:30:39.300
Sounds good.

00:30:39.300 --> 00:30:41.587
That's all for today.

00:30:41.587 --> 00:30:42.856
- Take care.
- Will do.

00:30:42.856 --> 00:30:44.915
Thank you.

00:30:45.820 --> 00:30:50.305
During the season, I don't have time
to focus on treatment.

00:30:50.305 --> 00:30:53.231
I'm playing through the pain.

00:30:53.231 --> 00:30:55.742
If anything, 200 million is still cheap.

00:30:56.442 --> 00:31:01.197
We have already told you the issue
is with your own personal maintenance.

00:31:02.535 --> 00:31:06.144
I've put my body on the line,
and fought for the team.

00:31:07.239 --> 00:31:10.465
Is that all you have to say to me?

00:31:11.185 --> 00:31:14.161
Managing injuries is a part of the sport.

00:31:17.795 --> 00:31:19.248
Alright then, fine.

00:31:20.717 --> 00:31:23.337
How much am I worth?

00:31:24.724 --> 00:31:26.715
60 million yen.

00:31:27.391 --> 00:31:28.938
Huh?

00:31:31.389 --> 00:31:34.037
Seriously.

00:31:34.037 --> 00:31:37.361
Amateurs don't understand anything.

00:31:38.922 --> 00:31:41.805
Feel my pain now?

00:31:43.764 --> 00:31:44.943
The hell, you bastard!

00:31:44.943 --> 00:31:47.911
"Bastard"? Way to talk to a woman.

00:31:49.057 --> 00:31:50.939
Negotiations are over.

00:31:52.483 --> 00:31:54.109
I suppose that's that.

00:32:01.421 --> 00:32:03.068
Damn it!

00:32:06.710 --> 00:32:08.681
I'm so pissed off!

00:32:08.681 --> 00:32:11.281
A player could have been hurt.

00:32:11.281 --> 00:32:15.363
Why are you so calm? He ruined your suit!

00:32:15.363 --> 00:32:16.677
It's nothing expensive.

00:32:16.677 --> 00:32:19.593
That's not the point.

00:32:21.937 --> 00:32:23.914
Thank you.

00:32:29.614 --> 00:32:33.390
Oh, no. I'm sorry for causing trouble.

00:32:37.408 --> 00:32:40.905
So, what do we do now?

00:32:40.905 --> 00:32:43.333
Not that it's my place to ask, but...

00:32:45.381 --> 00:32:47.568
If pushing doesn't work,

00:32:47.568 --> 00:32:49.230
we pull back.

00:32:53.851 --> 00:32:56.427
Alright, you convinced me.

00:32:56.427 --> 00:32:58.223
I'm in.

00:32:59.069 --> 00:33:02.102
Great, I've been waiting for that answer!

00:33:02.102 --> 00:33:05.446
Now your lifetime income will double.

00:33:05.446 --> 00:33:07.996
So, what should I do?

00:33:09.008 --> 00:33:12.229
If pushing doesn't work, you pull back.

00:33:15.936 --> 00:33:18.726
I spoke with Mr. Kijima.

00:33:19.797 --> 00:33:22.088
He's retiring.

00:33:23.734 --> 00:33:25.112
I see.

00:33:25.901 --> 00:33:27.452
I'm sorry.

00:33:28.943 --> 00:33:30.338
You did your best.

00:33:30.338 --> 00:33:31.715
Whoa!

00:33:31.715 --> 00:33:34.782
Don't flinch. I'm not always punchy.

00:33:34.782 --> 00:33:36.876
- Idiot!
- Hey! Not fair!

00:33:36.876 --> 00:33:38.890
It's called a feint. Deal with it.

00:33:38.890 --> 00:33:40.238
What's a feint?

00:33:40.238 --> 00:33:42.471
Hey, woah!

00:33:42.471 --> 00:33:44.859
Why are you laughing?

00:33:44.859 --> 00:33:46.024
What's wrong?

00:33:46.024 --> 00:33:49.174
Why did you suddenly
consider taking the season off?

00:33:50.283 --> 00:33:52.444
I got a bit of advice from someone.

00:33:52.444 --> 00:33:56.531
They said managing injuries
is a part of the sport.

00:33:57.460 --> 00:33:59.316
They gave me the push I needed

00:33:59.316 --> 00:34:03.624
to go fix this bothersome knee of mine.

00:34:03.624 --> 00:34:07.593
Though I'll be in rehab all next season,

00:34:07.593 --> 00:34:09.909
I'll make sure to fully recover,

00:34:09.909 --> 00:34:12.567
and prepare for my time as a free agent.

00:34:12.567 --> 00:34:14.142
What?

00:34:14.142 --> 00:34:16.353
- A free agent?
- Seriously?

00:34:16.353 --> 00:34:18.852
You're leaving the Dreams?

00:34:18.852 --> 00:34:21.013
I don't know about that.

00:34:21.013 --> 00:34:22.678
But here's the thing.

00:34:23.511 --> 00:34:27.011
I want to play baseball
for a team that respects me.

00:34:27.011 --> 00:34:30.120
And the Dreams don't?

00:34:30.120 --> 00:34:32.151
I'll leave that to your imagination.

00:34:32.151 --> 00:34:34.529
He can't just take the whole season off
without prior notice!

00:34:34.529 --> 00:34:39.076
If he keeps this up,
it'll affect our other players, right?

00:34:39.076 --> 00:34:40.769
As if negotiations weren't difficult enough.

00:34:40.769 --> 00:34:45.148
Iwata, fans consider you
their "last hope" for the Dreams.

00:34:59.220 --> 00:35:01.282
Iwata has chosen to take the season off.

00:35:01.282 --> 00:35:04.352
Have salary negotiations fallen through?

00:35:04.352 --> 00:35:07.693
As the team owner representative,
what are your thoughts on his withdrawal?

00:35:07.693 --> 00:35:09.786
Did Iwata make this decision on his own?

00:35:09.786 --> 00:35:11.541
Please answer us.

00:35:12.457 --> 00:35:16.062
- If we hear no answers...
- Folks, please. Please.

00:35:16.062 --> 00:35:21.249
The team is always committed
to putting the players first.

00:35:21.249 --> 00:35:27.077
We will persistently continue
amicable negotiations with Iwata.

00:35:27.077 --> 00:35:33.720
However, if we are unable
to satisfy our players...

00:35:35.919 --> 00:35:37.918
- Sir?
- Then what?

00:35:37.918 --> 00:35:40.328
President Negishi, please explain.

00:35:40.328 --> 00:35:42.910
Then perhaps the team...

00:35:43.737 --> 00:35:47.644
has no reason to exist.

00:35:47.644 --> 00:35:50.504
Does that mean the team will be disbanded?

00:35:50.504 --> 00:35:54.006
Will the Dreams merge with another team?

00:35:55.343 --> 00:35:58.360
President Negishi, please answer.

00:35:58.360 --> 00:36:00.719
What's going to happen?

00:36:00.719 --> 00:36:02.057
Come in.

00:36:03.904 --> 00:36:05.410
Excuse me.

00:36:06.506 --> 00:36:08.579
Is it done?

00:36:08.579 --> 00:36:09.873
Yes.

00:36:12.541 --> 00:36:14.211
Thank you.

00:36:15.129 --> 00:36:16.588
What's that?

00:36:22.910 --> 00:36:26.022
It's like you're always around.

00:36:27.893 --> 00:36:31.059
The Vikings' backup catcher.

00:36:33.129 --> 00:36:36.281
What about him?

00:36:37.212 --> 00:36:41.175
The Vikings already have Yoshida,
who you all drafted last year.

00:36:41.826 --> 00:36:44.365
You ought to give him a chance.

00:36:44.365 --> 00:36:46.726
Mind your own business!

00:36:49.722 --> 00:36:54.467
I always knew you were a shrewd man.

00:36:54.467 --> 00:36:58.012
But to think you even keep tabs
on our minor league players.

00:36:58.691 --> 00:37:00.540
Impressive.

00:37:05.159 --> 00:37:07.831
I knew it!

00:37:07.831 --> 00:37:11.775
You're trying to poach from us again?

00:37:11.775 --> 00:37:16.591
I believe it'll be a good deal,
for the both of us.

00:37:17.670 --> 00:37:21.402
Unbelievable...

00:37:26.077 --> 00:37:30.759
I deeply regret my actions.

00:37:30.759 --> 00:37:32.754
I don't trust you at all.

00:37:32.754 --> 00:37:33.992
No, please. Please.

00:37:33.992 --> 00:37:37.310
Please, look at the person I am now.

00:37:37.310 --> 00:37:40.099
Not the person I used to be! Please!

00:37:40.099 --> 00:37:42.517
I will be looking with watchful eyes.

00:37:45.797 --> 00:37:47.128
Yes, ma'am.

00:37:50.666 --> 00:37:53.042
- Sit down.
- I don't deserve to sit.

00:37:53.042 --> 00:37:54.579
- Next.
- I'll sit. Excuse me.

00:37:54.579 --> 00:37:58.509
We'll be drafting active players this month.

00:37:58.509 --> 00:38:00.786
Could you make a list of our candidates?

00:38:00.786 --> 00:38:01.932
Sure thing.

00:38:01.932 --> 00:38:04.948
Which position is the GM
looking to strengthen?

00:38:04.948 --> 00:38:10.078
The GM is looking for catchers, outfielders,
and utility infielders.

00:38:10.078 --> 00:38:12.056
"Utility"? In layman's terms, please.

00:38:12.056 --> 00:38:15.958
You, English, study, more.

00:38:15.958 --> 00:38:19.087
I can't believe you two.
Brush up your English!

00:38:19.087 --> 00:38:20.842
- He's definitely not sorry.
- I am sorry.

00:38:20.842 --> 00:38:24.824
In other words, a versatile player.

00:38:24.824 --> 00:38:28.819
Versatile? We have Nara for that, right?

00:38:28.819 --> 00:38:32.453
That's right. That's Nara's position.

00:38:32.453 --> 00:38:36.478
The GM's looking to trade him.

00:38:36.478 --> 00:38:37.897
Trade Nara?

00:38:37.897 --> 00:38:40.839
- Yes.
- What's the deal looking like?

00:38:40.839 --> 00:38:44.196
Three younger players, for one Nara.

00:38:46.296 --> 00:38:49.383
Regarding the email I sent earlier...

00:38:49.383 --> 00:38:52.123
Yes, the meeting just ended.

00:38:52.123 --> 00:38:54.758
The GM's prediction was right.

00:38:54.758 --> 00:38:58.085
Sorry or not, he's still a bootlicker.

00:38:58.085 --> 00:39:03.510
But now, with that shorty
spreading trade rumors,

00:39:03.510 --> 00:39:05.753
the unsigned players...

00:39:05.753 --> 00:39:07.753
Will definitely start to panic.

00:39:10.246 --> 00:39:11.374
- Yay!
- Ow!

00:39:11.374 --> 00:39:13.531
There's nothing "yay" about pain...

00:39:17.688 --> 00:39:19.426
What's with the tension, eh?

00:39:19.426 --> 00:39:20.847
Evening, sir.

00:39:20.847 --> 00:39:23.919
You all should've settled in.

00:39:23.919 --> 00:39:25.383
Sorry, sir.

00:39:25.383 --> 00:39:26.890
Sit, sit.

00:39:26.890 --> 00:39:28.096
If you'll excuse us.

00:39:28.096 --> 00:39:30.000
- Wine?
- Yeah.

00:39:33.634 --> 00:39:35.114
There you go.

00:39:36.916 --> 00:39:39.645
Sir, the GM is looking to fill our positions.

00:39:39.645 --> 00:39:45.009
Hey. Don't get swayed by stupid rumors.

00:39:45.009 --> 00:39:50.796
Mr. Sakurazaki has spoken
to the Pelicans and the Vikings.

00:39:50.796 --> 00:39:53.817
They've even discussed our trades.

00:39:53.817 --> 00:39:55.052
Listen.

00:39:55.052 --> 00:40:00.043
Mr. Nagai of the Pelicans
is just as stubborn as Sakurazaki.

00:40:00.043 --> 00:40:02.372
A trade won't be happening.

00:40:02.372 --> 00:40:04.443
What about Mr. Ishikura?

00:40:04.443 --> 00:40:08.967
They're still wrapping up
the Sawada-Kudo deal.

00:40:08.967 --> 00:40:11.947
There's no way he'd agree to a trade!

00:40:11.947 --> 00:40:16.224
Wouldn't it be better
if we just signed the team's offer?

00:40:16.224 --> 00:40:18.029
I'd like to resume training.

00:40:18.029 --> 00:40:21.477
That's why you guys get taken advantage of.

00:40:21.477 --> 00:40:25.405
Are you really satisfied
with such a low salary?

00:40:25.405 --> 00:40:28.272
Well? Are you?

00:40:29.839 --> 00:40:34.271
Only the Dreams would put us
on their starting lineup.

00:40:37.350 --> 00:40:40.942
I have mortgages I need to pay.

00:40:40.942 --> 00:40:43.712
My kids are also against moving.

00:40:43.712 --> 00:40:46.250
If I'm traded, I'd be living alone.

00:40:46.250 --> 00:40:50.353
We only entrusted the negotiations to you.

00:40:51.196 --> 00:40:53.773
We have no intention on leaving the team.

00:40:59.606 --> 00:41:01.592
Sorry, sir.

00:41:02.694 --> 00:41:04.244
Sorry.

00:41:05.004 --> 00:41:06.964
[GM Sakurazaki]

00:41:28.648 --> 00:41:30.407
We've been waiting for you.

00:41:30.407 --> 00:41:31.903
Where's the GM?

00:41:31.903 --> 00:41:35.987
He's out. He'll return in due time.

00:41:35.987 --> 00:41:37.950
He's the one who called me here.

00:41:37.950 --> 00:41:41.571
And I'll entertain you in the meantime.

00:41:48.017 --> 00:41:50.811
What the hell are you guys plotting?

00:42:00.551 --> 00:42:01.975
GM.

00:42:02.909 --> 00:42:07.397
Kato, will you really allow your agent
to handle everything?

00:42:08.963 --> 00:42:10.917
What are you doing here?

00:42:12.463 --> 00:42:14.776
Taking a walk.

00:42:14.776 --> 00:42:18.607
And while I'm at it,
I came to negotiate a salary.

00:42:22.715 --> 00:42:24.405
I'm sorry.

00:42:25.187 --> 00:42:28.242
No matter how difficult
negotiations are going,

00:42:28.242 --> 00:42:30.787
I just can't betray Kurokawa.

00:42:34.056 --> 00:42:36.441
Instead of thinking about him,

00:42:36.441 --> 00:42:38.937
why don't you think about yourself?

00:42:50.583 --> 00:42:52.599
What is this?

00:42:52.599 --> 00:42:57.946
This is an estimation
of the opportunities you'd see,

00:42:57.946 --> 00:43:01.024
and the lifetime salary you'd earn
on another team.

00:43:04.416 --> 00:43:07.141
From what I can tell,

00:43:07.141 --> 00:43:09.534
your prospects elsewhere are less than ideal.

00:43:15.740 --> 00:43:17.717
Would you like to continue negotiating?

00:43:24.001 --> 00:43:28.823
Negotiating behind the agent's back
is unacceptable.

00:43:28.823 --> 00:43:32.067
Now, hold on. The attorney is the agent.

00:43:32.067 --> 00:43:35.079
You're not a relevant party here.

00:43:35.079 --> 00:43:36.697
Fools.

00:43:36.697 --> 00:43:41.305
A 30 million yen contract?
Kato would never sign that.

00:43:42.664 --> 00:43:45.002
You think so?

00:43:55.756 --> 00:43:57.415
Coffee for you.

00:43:59.470 --> 00:44:03.482
That's piping hot.
I drink my coffee ice cold.

00:44:03.482 --> 00:44:08.039
Sorry. I was worried
you'd freeze up from the shock.

00:44:08.039 --> 00:44:11.944
Don't get cocky. Bring me an iced coffee.

00:44:11.944 --> 00:44:14.350
Oh! Nice!

00:44:14.350 --> 00:44:17.578
Seems like Kato signed the contract.

00:44:17.578 --> 00:44:18.636
What?

00:44:18.636 --> 00:44:20.237
Want to see it?

00:44:27.587 --> 00:44:30.911
Nara, can I talk to you for a minute?

00:44:30.911 --> 00:44:34.885
Please direct your negotiating to Kurokawa.

00:44:37.715 --> 00:44:39.255
What's your desired salary?

00:44:39.255 --> 00:44:43.585
Like I said, I don't know. Ask our agent.

00:44:43.585 --> 00:44:47.955
Did he tell you our GM
offered you 60 million yen next year?

00:44:50.375 --> 00:44:52.265
Huh?

00:44:52.265 --> 00:44:54.430
Is that still not enough?

00:44:59.566 --> 00:45:05.217
Kurokawa signed with you all
instead of a free agent for a reason.

00:45:07.919 --> 00:45:09.779
Kurokawa is like...

00:45:11.184 --> 00:45:13.394
A big brother to us.

00:45:13.394 --> 00:45:14.959
So you say...

00:45:16.347 --> 00:45:18.788
But he's forcing favors onto you all.

00:45:24.081 --> 00:45:27.180
Would you really call that
an act of goodwill?

00:45:33.022 --> 00:45:37.356
No other team would offer you 60 million yen.

00:45:38.363 --> 00:45:41.018
Please give it some more thought.

00:45:48.846 --> 00:45:51.410
We've got another signed deal.

00:45:57.003 --> 00:45:59.476
Damn it.

00:45:59.476 --> 00:46:02.215
Can you please leave already?

00:46:02.929 --> 00:46:05.806
You're the one who called me here.

00:46:05.806 --> 00:46:07.829
Quit fooling around!

00:46:07.829 --> 00:46:09.956
We're nothing but serious, sir!

00:46:11.060 --> 00:46:17.845
We are dedicating our bodies and souls
to protect the team.

00:46:17.845 --> 00:46:20.761
You've made players and their families suffer

00:46:20.761 --> 00:46:24.968
all because of some selfish revenge.

00:46:26.807 --> 00:46:30.407
You really think you've won with this?

00:46:31.973 --> 00:46:33.946
Please leave.

00:46:35.209 --> 00:46:36.727
Damn it.

00:46:45.474 --> 00:46:48.204
[Nara: I've signed the deal. Sorry.]
[Kato: I signed the contract.]

00:46:49.736 --> 00:46:52.011
Damn it.

00:47:00.299 --> 00:47:03.309
So, you're saying the cause of your defeat

00:47:03.309 --> 00:47:08.410
is this new salary assessment sheet?

00:47:14.335 --> 00:47:16.843
Indeed.

00:47:16.843 --> 00:47:21.589
It covers all sorts of potential earnings,
and opportunities.

00:47:21.589 --> 00:47:27.877
It's no wonder the players felt shaken,
and signed their contracts.

00:47:30.481 --> 00:47:33.656
Did you truly think
I'd be so easily convinced?

00:47:36.030 --> 00:47:37.505
Please wait.

00:47:37.505 --> 00:47:40.850
We still have Iwata, the starting catcher.

00:47:40.850 --> 00:47:44.183
I will definitely prevent him from signing.

00:47:48.537 --> 00:47:52.994
I'm really counting on you.

00:47:54.052 --> 00:47:56.712
Really.

00:48:20.144 --> 00:48:22.464
[Written by Akito Sakurazaki]

00:48:23.471 --> 00:48:27.790
Akito... Sakurazaki?

00:48:33.346 --> 00:48:37.094
Do you still have an excuse, Mr. Kurokawa?

00:48:42.594 --> 00:48:44.001
Hey.

00:48:47.072 --> 00:48:49.098
The contracts.

00:48:49.098 --> 00:48:51.114
Thank you.

00:48:51.114 --> 00:48:55.115
Our plan was a huge success.

00:48:55.115 --> 00:48:57.097
Yes!

00:48:57.097 --> 00:49:00.105
All thanks to "our" efforts, right?

00:49:00.105 --> 00:49:01.911
You want a compliment.

00:49:01.911 --> 00:49:03.940
- Yes, yes, good job.
- Ow, ow, ow, ow!

00:49:03.940 --> 00:49:06.303
I don't need that kind of reward!

00:49:06.303 --> 00:49:08.981
All that's left is that cocky Iwata.

00:49:08.981 --> 00:49:10.593
Potty mouth.

00:49:10.593 --> 00:49:12.923
Says who?

00:49:12.923 --> 00:49:14.458
You.

00:49:14.458 --> 00:49:16.023
Ow!

00:49:16.023 --> 00:49:18.769
It hurts, right? I bear with that every day.

00:49:18.769 --> 00:49:20.480
Ouch...

00:49:20.480 --> 00:49:22.717
Well, well.

00:49:23.503 --> 00:49:27.397
I knew the GM would get you.

00:49:28.757 --> 00:49:31.177
It's not over yet.

00:49:31.177 --> 00:49:33.908
You can't win.

00:49:33.908 --> 00:49:36.715
You can't sell.

00:49:36.715 --> 00:49:40.807
You can't even destroy a baseball team.

00:49:43.551 --> 00:49:47.039
You can't do anything.

00:49:51.106 --> 00:49:54.063
Just like your father.

00:49:57.173 --> 00:49:58.576
What?

00:50:00.346 --> 00:50:04.419
Did I say something wrong?

00:50:07.701 --> 00:50:09.609
It's not over yet.

00:50:29.072 --> 00:50:30.441
Good morning!

00:50:31.354 --> 00:50:33.188
- Hey, Iwata.
- Yeah?

00:50:33.188 --> 00:50:36.172
Are you really taking next season off?

00:50:37.958 --> 00:50:40.065
It's part of the negotiation.

00:50:40.065 --> 00:50:42.049
I just want more money.

00:50:43.277 --> 00:50:45.346
Don't worry.

00:50:45.346 --> 00:50:48.166
I'm ready to catch your pitches next season.

00:50:53.412 --> 00:50:55.767
Mr. Kijima's retirement...

00:50:55.767 --> 00:50:57.748
It's our fault, isn't it?

00:51:01.419 --> 00:51:03.790
Let's plan a retirement ceremony for him.

00:51:04.860 --> 00:51:09.338
I'm impressed we even signed on so many
with a 30% budget cut.

00:51:13.599 --> 00:51:15.719
The players...

00:51:17.184 --> 00:51:19.498
What do they think of us right now?

00:51:21.894 --> 00:51:24.028
We trampled on their pride,

00:51:25.400 --> 00:51:27.931
exploited their weaknesses,

00:51:27.931 --> 00:51:31.368
and offered amounts unworthy
of their true value.

00:51:33.672 --> 00:51:36.657
We made them make some difficult decisions.

00:51:38.190 --> 00:51:41.228
The one who ordered the cut
was President Negishi.

00:51:52.582 --> 00:51:57.233
There still might be something we can do.

00:52:33.313 --> 00:52:34.792
Well, well, GM.

00:52:34.792 --> 00:52:37.515
No knock? What do you want?

00:52:37.515 --> 00:52:38.567
What's the meaning of this?

00:52:38.567 --> 00:52:40.254
[Dreams GM, Employing his Jobless Brother?]

00:52:40.254 --> 00:52:41.449
[Abusing his authority]

00:52:41.449 --> 00:52:43.789
[Employing his Jobless Brother?]

00:52:44.764 --> 00:52:47.791
What? Has there been some sort of mistake?

00:52:47.791 --> 00:52:49.264
It's full of mistakes.

00:52:49.264 --> 00:52:53.382
Both this article,
and your behavior as owner representative.

00:52:54.889 --> 00:52:58.836
You're the one full of mistakes.

00:52:58.836 --> 00:53:01.901
If this article comes out
at the start of the week,

00:53:01.901 --> 00:53:05.023
those contracts you worked so hard to secure?

00:53:05.023 --> 00:53:08.940
They'll likely be canceled
by a number of players.

00:53:10.491 --> 00:53:12.819
Withdraw this headline, now.

00:53:15.379 --> 00:53:18.587
Is that how you ask your superior
for a favor?

00:53:18.587 --> 00:53:21.812
It's not if I had a respectable superior.

00:53:23.451 --> 00:53:25.566
Bow your head.

00:53:30.688 --> 00:53:34.032
Bow your head to me!

00:53:35.179 --> 00:53:37.662
If the article comes out,
your brother will be fired,

00:53:37.662 --> 00:53:40.590
and the players will rebel.

00:53:40.590 --> 00:53:44.563
If you want me to withdraw it,
obey my command.

00:53:44.563 --> 00:53:46.257
So?

00:53:46.257 --> 00:53:49.768
An organization who controls with fear...

00:53:49.768 --> 00:53:51.559
has no future!

00:53:53.621 --> 00:53:59.181
Are you suggesting you're any better?

00:53:59.820 --> 00:54:07.964
You've used every trick in the book
to make weaker players submit to you.

00:54:10.677 --> 00:54:13.271
As long as you're in this organization,

00:54:15.930 --> 00:54:19.809
throw away your lukewarm sense of justice.

00:54:19.809 --> 00:54:22.977
Give up your beliefs!

00:54:22.977 --> 00:54:28.000
Here is my first command.

00:54:28.000 --> 00:54:32.993
It may very well be my last.

00:54:35.439 --> 00:54:38.654
The GM had a two-year contract.

00:54:38.654 --> 00:54:42.158
Even if he didn't do the proper work,

00:54:42.158 --> 00:54:46.371
I would pay him the two year salary.

00:54:47.510 --> 00:54:50.976
But there are reasons to fire the GM.

00:54:50.976 --> 00:54:52.661
First.

00:54:53.500 --> 00:54:56.352
He botched salary negotiations,

00:54:56.352 --> 00:55:00.771
and drew public critique
when our starting catcher

00:55:00.771 --> 00:55:04.117
announced he'd take the season off.

00:55:04.117 --> 00:55:06.041
Second.

00:55:07.530 --> 00:55:14.358
He illegally hired his jobless brother
as a data analyst,

00:55:14.358 --> 00:55:16.533
thus disgracing the team.

00:55:16.533 --> 00:55:18.812
Third.

00:55:23.176 --> 00:55:25.575
He's insolent.

00:55:26.523 --> 00:55:32.163
Insolent and utterly infuriating.

00:55:33.884 --> 00:55:37.105
If you want to protect your brother
and the team,

00:55:38.912 --> 00:55:42.235
resign as GM.

00:55:47.006 --> 00:55:50.238
Get out of here!